 However  I  am  quite sure it won't do anything wrong - I tested it for 
hours on my private local line.
 It  has  also  been tested remotely at several BBS'es. It worked safely
at  the  time  of release. I won't say it worked 100% because it didn't, 
but  it  worked safely.  It didn't bomb out, or log me off, or anything. 
Sometimes  it  did  throw  up an error and return me to the BBS, but who 
cares.. Just run it again. @{b}If you don't like it, don't use it.@{ub}

 To  help  prevent piracy, as from v1.30 the registered user's name will 
be  hard-coded  into  the  executable and is displayed while the program 
loads.  If  I see any bogus copies I will take action against the people 
involved. The startup delay is NOT intentional - it is NECESSARY for the 
program to parse it's config and set up.

